column5: Or the little student in one of my schools. Justin Case. For what were not sure

I know a guy called, Marcel Mallot...pronounced "MALLO"....   what is short for Marcel?  Marce...Mallot....."MARSHMALLOW"  how bout a guy I went to College with  Horace Runhing....horse running.  Justin Case.... self explanatory  I also know of a SF resident called   Richard Head.....figure it out ... he's now called Dave.  some peoples parents Sheesh...!!
Buster Hyman  This one is real - Dick Hancock.

I deliver mail to the Wong house every day . . . .    I used to occasionally deliver to the Wright house too. Also had a customer called Katie O'Snatch . . . . .     just a few houses away from Ya Ping Yan.
Dick Incyder
Now imagine if you went to the Orient and your name was Ron Mower.  An aquaintence through work has a friend, Craven Moorehead.
I know a guy "Fuk Yu" Pronounce-- Screw U. Not that I have a cool name, my last name is not funny (maybe) but is KANAGASUNTHERI, say that 10 times..heheheheheh

A few years ago in the Hamilton phone book was a Hue G Rection ...honestly   But the best is our present landscape maintnance guy at the plant    Richard Phallis and No word of lie he replaced Hugh Johnson. We stilll laugh about this!
Not sure what it is called now but there was a pub in Toronto on the Danforth near Coxwell avenue called The Coxwell Inn...
harry beaver, no kidding lol
I worked with a guy named Pornpak.  It always made me think of the cabel TV.  If you liked sports you could order the Sports Pack.  If you prefer other forms of entertainment you could order the ...
There was a teacher named Patti Hamburger and a dutch doode name Dick Wanker. Thats not how his last name was spelt but pronounced.
Harri Palm is a local musician here in Guelph, he usually plays alone!
Y'all have to remember a few Classic Austin Powers names.........Ivana Humpalot........Allota Fagina........Phook Yu and her sister Phook Mi..........lol
Rod Siemen  Peter Peters

There's a road a few miles from my home called "DUMB HUNDRED ROAD".   Word has it that there were about 100 people living along that back road many years back and all 100 of them were  ...... .    We'll you know.

Geez...grade school must've been some fun for you, eh?  My last name is pronounced "shoot."  You can imagine the roll call when I took hunter's ed & the gun course.  I know a physiotherapist named Payne.  My nomination for the awards roster:  Dick Hyman, the organist.    (official site & wikipedia)  Ancestry.com recently put together a book of the worst names they encountered while digitizing records.  There's a bit of a sample backgrounder, and a blog by the author.  Gotta love JJ Walker's 5 sons in the 1860 census:  Bud, Little Bud, Buddy, Little Buddy, and Least Buddy.
One of my old clients name is Tom Pon....I did a double take on that one!!!  LOL!!   Chrispy!

Had a Captain who's best friend's Name Rank and name were: Major W H O R E. He instructed us not to laugh especially when he introduced us. Two weeks later, the week before we were to meet him he was promoted to Lt. Colonel. Would have been tough saying welcome to the SQN and using his name& rank  Ahh if you write w hore it puts in checkout girl
I had a couple of funny customer names:  twit Chow Joanna Porko
Just got another one.  Our UPS drivers name is Miles Long.
And if a girls last name is "Dyke", which way are you going to pronounce it?  Ask that one in front of 24 students.
I used to date a van Dyke, actually I dated two cause there was a sister.  they seemed to be proud of their name.  Maybe there was something I didn't know about?
Harry Wong  (My boss at a chinese food restaurant when i was a teen)  Dick long (though he preferred Richard)
Try Holly Passafume. Say that with a straight face in front of a class the first day of school. And Yes, I was correctd it is pronounced PASS-A-FUME!  muddler
There was a girl who went to a neighboring high school who's name was Krystal Shanda Lier
I grew up in a town with the Hole family, one of the girls was Rosie, and one of the boys was named..............you guessed it..Doug.
I went to High school with a guy names Andrew Hopf (HOFF) and his father's name was Jack. You put it together!

Anybody know Dick Hurtz from Beeton,or his cousin Dick Shrivel from Coldwater???LOL.....But seriously while in Ayr On. I saw a relestate sign with the name Gaye Males as the broker......TC and tight lines.....Chuck.....

On my route there is a beef farm with a big sign Kuntz Cattle and right across the road their name acording to an even bigger sign is Slitz....... I admit I always chuckle when I get near the Kuntz and Slitz farms...
TJ told us his real name once.
...  don't you dare......
I've had that disease they named after him and it aint no fun!!!
No worries, Tref, your secret is safe with me.  BTW, are you smelling like clover, or is it just me?
how bout nascar driver Dick Trickle? or US Olympian Peekaboo Street?
Whats it worth T.J?? A hat, t-shirt, ohhh wait you have already given me those. Ok lips sealed buddy!!
Real estate broker...sign in oshawa - Poon Tang  No word of a lie, was on a house right beside a best friends!
Neal Enbob harry ballsonia
A friend of mine pointed this one out to me.......in the Niagara Falls phone book. First name: Harry..... last name: Hiscocks.... but in the phonebook it's last name first...first name last.

Ok, I know this isn't fishing related but I figured "What the heck"....  I was wondering if anybody has any examples of funny but real names. Names that you would think...."nah....that can be a real name!!".....  I was listening to the radio and heard of Toronto's director of transportation services.......His name is.... Peter Noehammer.....  I'm sure he got/gets some ribbing .  Anyone else have any too funny but real names?  Meely  PS: Yes , I'm bored.....and Crappy dont open for another 5 weeks or so !!
Mike Hunt,Ben Dover, Amir Cinder,John Fitzpatrick,Toucan Chu..
Hugh Jass!!
I went to school with Mike Hawk... maybe a few of th Bronte OFNer's remember him.

Honest to God...  Dudes name on a Fly Fishing show that I see on WFN. Can't remember the name of the show, but it's hosted or produced (can't remember) by...get ready... Jack Imhoff.  Parents can be cruel.   Hookset.   Oh Ya...my Bass Tourney partner...Perry Mason (how can we lose ?)
Lady that worked at the neighborhood restaurant Iona Nipple, what lost one?
Ima Hoar and Shi' Thead Watson

A former boss was named Ginger, when she married, she became Ginger Snapp  I was confirming party reservations the other day and the young lady on the phone's name....Carley Davidson, guess her parents were hoping for a boy....
Mary Seeman, and then there was Vladamere Agupoo (pronounced ag-u-poo) in High school.  What a Nerd.
Anne Teak Barb Dwyer Joe King Rick 0'shea Lance Boyle
A couple of people I know in real life.  Dik Cox, tried to convince him to name his son Harry, but the wife wouldn't go for it?  Went to school with Iona Johnson, she's a girl maybe?
Well there's always my fave - Dick Trickle of racing fame.  A friend of mine is named Heather and she married Don Leather, so her name is now  Heather Leather!!

When my son was born we named him Sam. When my daughter was born, we seriously considered naming her "Ella" so I could then introduce my kids to people as.... yes you guessed it... "Sam 'n Ella"! LOL In my business, I am confronted with many funny and strange names. Here's a few: -Goopertop - I always wondered if his top was goopy, what would his bottom be like! Ouch! -Norm Mole = Normal! Funny he was anything but! HH

Hey my mother was gonna call me Rick...  Had a guy that I worked with at Consumers Glass in Milton... last name was Coke. When their son was born they thought it was hillarious that they had named him Ryan !

My chiropractor and old team mate in our thursday night hockey....Larry Down. Which doesn't really mean anything unless you get his middle name as well, which happens to be Neale. I never met him until we where adults, but he told me he used to get ribbed alot when he was younger.

They had a radio contest a few years back, and this dude actually changed his name to "Haywood Jablome". The things people will do for money.....  Also, a former client of mine was named "Fanny Poon". (no word of a lie)
I had a girl in my grade 10 english class, Jennifer Blows, she had 3 sisters...not going there..
Did you date any of them????
OH, just remembered one....  one of my wifes clients... "Dick Cummerford"
that would of been even crueler......
Swear this is true- Jurgen Knopf. It was VERY difficult to hold a straight face writing up the workorder.  Also a good friend of mine Peter Piper. Also worked with Tom and "Buzz" Sawyer.
Peter File, Harry Bird.
I knew a guy who used to tell me about a kid he went to school with named Richard Tamer. Hell....my last name is Reddick! lol  -R
girl at school was Teressa Green, always asked her if her sisters name was Grassis worked with an old guy named Tom Bowler, lady at home Eileen Dover, she took some stick when she had a drink,,,lol
Yes went to the same school but do you also rember we had a Mike Hunt as well made for some funny announcments
